# Auto-deploy (Flutter web)

A user-level Cursor `stop` hook builds and deploys Flutter web to Firebase Hosting (`souschef-ai`) when an agent session ends and relevant files have uncommitted changes (`lib/`, `web/`, `assets/`, `pubspec.yaml`, `pubspec.lock`).

- Do **not** manually run `flutter build web` + `firebase deploy --only hosting` unless the user explicitly asks or the hook failed (check `~/.cursor/hooks/logs/deploy-recipeai.log`).
- Focus on code changes; deployment is handled after the session completes.
